President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for various positions. Lee Philip Rudofsky of Arkansas is nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Eastern District of Arkansas. Rudofsky is currently the Senior Director for Global Anti-Corruption Compliance at Walmart Inc. Prior to joining Walmart, he served as Solicitor General of Arkansas and was in private practice at Kirkland & Ellis, LLP. He earned his B.S. from Cornell University, his M.P.A. from the Cornell Institute of Public Affairs, and his J.D. from Harvard Law School.

R. Austin Huffaker, Jr. of Alabama is nominated to serve as a Judge on the U.S. District Court for the Middle District of Alabama. Huffaker is a Shareholder at Rushton, Stakely, Johnston & Garrett, P.A., specializing in complex commercial, product and lender liability, and professional malpractice litigation. He earned his B.Eng. from Vanderbilt University and his J.D. from the University of Alabama.

Kerry Lee Pettingill of Oklahoma is nominated to serve as United States Marshal for the Eastern District of Oklahoma. Pettingill is currently the Corporate Director of Department of Transportation Compliance for Quintana Energy Services, Inc. He has a long career in law enforcement, serving as the Director of the Oklahoma Office of Homeland Security and as a member of the Oklahoma Highway Patrol. He earned his B.S. from Southern Nazarene University.